comments.en: This is the Materials Design Ontology.

comment.en: ComputationalMethod stand for the methods used in computer simulations for materials according to theories.
To represent an element in the periodic table.
LengthTriple consists of three bases of a unit cell.

seeAlso.value: International Tables for Crystallography, Volume A, Fourth, revised edition, Section 8.1.5.

comment.en: A group of linear mappings of vector space, which is corresonpond to the group of motions in point space determining the symmetry of the macroscopic crystal, is called the point group of the crystal, furthermore of the crystal structure, and is also called the point group of its space group.

comment.undefined: SoftwareAgent represents which software produces the result of a material calculation.

comment.en: Lattice is a set of points abstracted from basis. A three-dimensional lattice can ve visualized best as an infinite periodic array of points.

comment.undefined: ReferenceAgent is used to represent the reference of materials data.

comment.en: Properties of structures or materials that are not influenced by calculations.
MaterialsData is a piece of data that represents materials calculation.
Hartree-Fock method is a method to get the approximation of the determination of the wave functiona and the energy of system in a stationary state.
A basis can be described by basis's length vector a, b, c and the intervector angles alpha, beta and gamma.
Calculation means using specific computational method to compute materials' electronic structure and get the relationships between materials properties and structures.

comment.undefined: DatabaseAgent represents which databases stores the material data.

comment.en: Each point in a lattice is a site.
Composition is used to represent the composition of chemical elements of structures.
Properties of structures or materials that are influenced by calculations.
Structure is a unit that is used in a materials calculation. It is a part of a specific material.
A material's property is an intensive property of some material.

seeAlso.value: International Tables for Crystallography, Volume !, Fourth, revised edition, Section 8.1.5.

comment.en: The symmetry group of a three-dimensional crystal pattern is called its space group.
Density functional theory is a computational quantum mechanical modelling method to investigate the electronic structure.
AngleTriple is a vector of three angles which represent the angles among three bases in a unit cell.
Species is the combination of atoms on each site.

seeAlso.value: The functionals to compute Exchange Correlation Energy.
